# Force LF line endings for committed markdown files.
#
# Why: data/processed_memory/*.md and data/memory/USER.md / MEMORY.md
# are hashed by MemoryCurator.compile_split_memory and recorded into
# the *.manifest.json source_hashes. Without this rule, Windows
# checkout normalises LF → CRLF in the working tree while the index
# stays LF, so MemoryCurator's read_bytes() hash drifts away from any
# manifest written on a Linux/WSL host (and vice-versa). The drift
# makes compile_split_memory report ``compile_reason=source_changed``
# every run even when no semantic change occurred — see the manifest
# parity report from the response_style import.
#
# Scope is intentionally narrow (markdown only) so other text formats
# keep their existing per-OS conventions until separately reviewed.
# Existing tracked .md files do NOT get rewritten by adding this file
# — run ``git add --renormalize .`` separately if you want to flush
# the working tree to LF immediately. That is out of scope for this
# commit.
*.md text eol=lf
